        <h1>Neal Smith Award Winners</h1>
<hr />
<p>The AMTA presents the Neal Smith Award to one individual annually in recognition of their "contributions to AMTA's educational mission" in a broader sense.</p>
<p>
The winners of the Neal Smith Award have made outstanding and exemplary contributions to law related education and its mission to promote public understanding of law and the legal process. </p>
<p>2024 - Joshua Leckrone, University of Cincinnati<br />
2023 - Anna Eldridge - Rhodes College<br />
2022 - Ed Stern, Boston University<br />
2021 - Justin Bernstein, Director of the A. Barry Cappello Program at UCLA Law, AMTA President (2014-2016)<br />
2020 - Toby Heytens, University of Virginia<br />
2019 - DeLois Leapheart, Northwood University<br />
2018 - Deborah Strigenz, Former Coordinator of the Iowa Center for Law-Related Education at Drake University<br />
2017 - Mark Graber, University of Maryland<br />
2016 - Dick Lesicko, Macalester College<br />
2015 - Michael Walsh, Loyola University - Chicago<br />
2014 - David Nelmark, Drake University, AMTA President (2010-2012)<br />
2013 - Barry Langford, Columbia College<br />
2012 - James Houlihan, Lewis University<br />
2011 - Dick Calkins, AMTA Founder, AMTA President (1984-2004)<br />
2010 - Ava Preacher, University of Notre Dame<br />
2009 - Gonzalo Freixes, University of California - Los Angeles<br />
2008 - Frank Guliuzza, Weber State University, AMTA President (2016-2018)<br />
2007 - Felicia Walker Stewart, Howard University<br />
2006 - Sara Zeigler, Eastern Kentucky University, AMTA President (2008-2010)<br />
2005 - Bob Boland, Manchester Community College<br />
2005 - Mark Pohlmann, Rhodes College, AMTA President (2006-2008)<br />
2004 - Dan Herron, Miami University<br />
2003 - Mary Lynn Neuhaus, Loras College<br />
2002 - Glen Halva-Neubauer, Furman University, AMTA President (2012-2014)<br />
2001 - Dan Stamatelos, AMTA co-founder<br />
2000 - John Vile, Middle Tennessee State University<br />
1999 - Mike Johnson, Buena Vista University and Iowa Lakes Community College<br />
1999 - Jim Wagoner, Bellarmine College, AMTA President (2004-2006)<br />
1998 - Jo Ann Scott, Ohio Northern University<br />
1997 - John McKiernan, University of South Dakota<br />
1996 - Faith O'Reilly, Hamline University<br />
1995 - Brad Bloch, University of Wisconsin - Milwaukee <br />
1994 - Judge Peter Handwork, University of Toledo <br />
1993 - Ruth Wagoner, Bellarmine College<br />
1992 - Peter Leigh, Eastern Illinois University<br />
1991 - Don Racheter, Central College</p>&nbsp;
      </div>
